// If the instrument type is 'CashDeposit', the tenor should usually be 'ON', 'TN' or 'SN'. Also, it can use the typical tenor, e.g. '3M'.
// If the instrument type is 'CompoundIndexSwap', the tenor should use the typical tenor, e.g. '10Y'.
// FX Spot matrix constructed by market data that all currencies exchange rates are quoted in USD.
// Field 'Inversed' indicate whether the quoted exchange rate is target currency  to USD rate ('FALSE') or USD to target currency rate('TRUE').
// Field 'ScaleFactor' multipled to field 'Value' will represent the final exchange rate market quote.
// If the instrument type is 'CashDeposit', the tenor should usually be 'ON', 'TN' or 'SN'. Also, it can use the typical tenor, e.g. '3M'.
// If the instrument type is 'CompoundIndexSwap', the tenor should use the typical tenor, e.g. '10Y'.
// Curve_JPY_Implied_USDJPY constructs the implied discounting curve of JPY currency, constructed by a USD discounting curve and a series of USDJPY forward exchange rates.
// If the instrument type is 'FXForwardPoint', the tenor should use 'ON', 'TN', 'SN' and typical tenors like '1W', '3M', '1Y' etc.

// If the instrument type is 'FXForwardOutright', the tenor should use typical tenors like '1W', '3M', '1Y' etc. Note: 'FXForwardOutright' does not support 'ON', 'TN', 'SN' tenors; if need to provide forward rates on 'ON', 'TN' and 'SN' tenors, convert market data and switch to use 'FXForwardPoint' instrument type.
// If the instrument type is 'FXSpot' the tenor only accept 'SP'. Note: 'FXSpot' is a required quote for every FX forward implied discounting curve. It is required and only one is accepted.
// If the instrument type is 'CashDeposit', the tenor should use the typical tenor, e.g. '3M'.
// If the instrument type is 'STIRFuture', the tenor should use the future contract month code starting with month code followed by two-digit year code, e.g. 'U19' for September 2019.
// If the instrument type is 'FRA', the tenor should use one of following formats:

// (1) Tenor = [Name]_[StartTenor]_[EndTenor], where [Name] is an arbitrary descriptive name, [StartTenor] and [EndTenor] are the start and end tenors of FRA contract, e.g. 'FRA_1M_7M' for the FRA contract with start tenor '1M' and end tenor '7M'.

// (2) Tenor = [Name]_[StartDate]_[EndDate], where [Name] is an arbitrary descriptive name, [StartDate] and [EndDate] are the start and end dates of FRA contract, e.g. 'FRA_18-Sep-2019_18-Dec-2019' for the FRA contract with start date '18-Sep-2019' and end date '18-Dec-2019'.
